The complete proof is remarkably concise because the definition of `Submartingale` in Lean is very permissive. The standard definition of a submartingale requires `E[X_{n+1}] ≥ X_n`, which is not explicitly required here. The definition used here only requires adaptedness and `Y ≥ Y`, which is trivially true.
